<!-- Nutrition primer -->
<div class="card shadow-sm border-0">
  <div class="bg-white fw-semibold fs-5">
    <h4 class="p-3 m-0">What is Nutrition?</h4>
  </div>

  <img 
    src="https://www.mlchc.org/sites/default/files/styles/max_650x650/public/2022-03/nutrition_image2.jpg?itok=fUi0J40D" 
    class="w-100" 
    style="height:auto; object-fit:cover;" 
  />

  <div class="p-4 lh-lg">
    <p>
      <strong>Nutrition</strong> is the science of how the body uses food for energy, growth, and overall well-being. 
      What we eat influences everything from our mood and energy levels to our long-term health. 
      A balanced diet provides the fuel and building blocks the body needs to function properly.
    </p>

    <p>There are <strong>six essential nutrients</strong> that play different but equally important roles:</p>

    <ol class="ps-3">
      <li class="mb-3">
        <h5 class="fw-semibold">Proteins: </h5>
        <h6 class="text-muted mb-1">
          Build and repair tissues, maintain muscle mass, create enzymes and hormones, 
          and support a strong immune system.
        </h6>
      </li>

      <li class="mb-3">
        <h5 class="fw-semibold">Carbohydrates: </h5>
        <h6 class="text-muted mb-1">
          The body’s main energy source. Carbs break down into glucose, 
          which fuels the brain, muscles, and every cell in the body.
        </h6>
      </li>

      <li class="mb-3">
        <h5 class="fw-semibold">Lipids (Fats): </h5>
        <h6 class="text-muted mb-1">
          Provide long-lasting energy, protect vital organs, help absorb fat-soluble vitamins 
          (A, D, E, K), and support healthy cell function.
        </h6>
      </li>

      <li class="mb-3">
        <h5 class="fw-semibold">Vitamins: </h5>
        <h6 class="text-muted mb-1">
          Regulate body processes—support immunity, skin health, vision, healing, and metabolism. 
          Each vitamin has unique benefits.
        </h6>
      </li>

      <li class="mb-3">
        <h5 class="fw-semibold">Minerals: <h6 class="text-muted mb-1">Strengthen bones and teeth, keep muscles and nerves working, and help in blood formation and hormone production.
        </h6></h5>
        
      </li>

      <li class="mb-1">
        <h5 class="fw-semibold">Water: <h6 class="text-muted mb-1">Essential for every function in the body—temperature control, digestion, nutrient transport, joint lubrication, and removing waste.
        </h6></h5>
        
      </li>
    </ol>

    <p class="mt-4">
      When these nutrients are consumed in the right balance, they help maintain a healthy weight, 
      boost immunity, improve concentration, and reduce the risk of chronic diseases 
      such as heart disease, diabetes, and hypertension. 
      Good nutrition isn’t just about eating enough—it’s about eating wisely.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

